articles.headline: Mix-Up Preceded Deadly Drone Strike in Jordan, U.S. Officials Say
articles.snippet: The attack on Sunday killed three Army reservists, the first known American military deaths from hostile fire in the turmoil spilling over from Israel’s war with Hamas.
articles.abstract: The attack on Sunday killed three Army reservists, the first known American military deaths from hostile fire in the turmoil spilling over from Israel’s war with Hamas.
articles.lead_paragraph: Air defenses failed to stop an attack on a U.S. military outpost in Jordan on Sunday that killed three American soldiers at least in part because the hostile drone approached its target at the same time an American drone was returning to the base, two U.S. officials said on Monday.

articles.headline: U.N. Agency for Palestinians Imperiled by Terrorism Charges
articles.snippet: Donors have pulled funds for the main aid agency in Gaza after allegations that some employees took part in the Oct. 7 attack, but it is not clear who would fill the vacuum if it ran out of money.
articles.abstract: Donors have pulled funds for the main aid agency in Gaza after allegations that some employees took part in the Oct. 7 attack, but it is not clear who would fill the vacuum if it ran out of money.
articles.lead_paragraph: Leaders of the largest United Nations agency in Gaza warned on Monday that it may soon run out of money as new allegations emerged about Hamas’s influence on the organization.
articles.byline: By Patrick Kingsley and Ronen Bergman

articles.headline: China’s Real Estate Crisis ‘Has Not Touched Bottom’
articles.snippet: The forced liquidation of China Evergrande epitomizes the sector’s struggles: Nationwide, sales are down and millions of homes have been paid for but not delivered.
articles.abstract: The forced liquidation of China Evergrande epitomizes the sector’s struggles: Nationwide, sales are down and millions of homes have been paid for but not delivered.
articles.lead_paragraph: The unwavering belief of Chinese home buyers that real estate was a can’t-lose investment propelled the country’s property sector to become the backbone of its economy.
articles.byline: By Daisuke Wakabayashi and Claire Fu

articles.headline: Why Cut Rates in an Economy This Strong? A Big Question Confronts the Fed.
articles.snippet: The central bank is widely expected to lower interest rates this year. But with growth and consumer spending chugging along, explaining it may take some work.
articles.abstract: The central bank is widely expected to lower interest rates this year. But with growth and consumer spending chugging along, explaining it may take some work.
articles.lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve is widely expected to leave interest rates unchanged at the conclusion of its meeting on Wednesday, but investors will be watching closely for any hint at when and how much it might lower those rates this year.

articles.headline: Focused Cuts and Fewer Layers: Tech Layoffs Enter a New Phase
articles.snippet: Amazon, Google, Microsoft and other tech companies have been on a layoff spree this month, with the latest cuts differing from last year’s mass reductions.
articles.abstract: Amazon, Google, Microsoft and other tech companies have been on a layoff spree this month, with the latest cuts differing from last year’s mass reductions.
articles.lead_paragraph: Last year, Mark Zuckerberg declared 2023 to be a “year of efficiency.” His company, Meta, soon laid off a third of its employees. Amazon, Google and Microsoft also cut tens of thousands of workers.

articles.headline: The War the World Can’t See
articles.snippet: From outside Gaza, the scale of death and destruction is impossible to grasp, shrouded by communications blackouts, restrictions barring international reporters and extreme challenges facing local journalists.
articles.abstract: From outside Gaza, the scale of death and destruction is impossible to grasp, shrouded by communications blackouts, restrictions barring international reporters and extreme challenges facing local journalists.
articles.lead_paragraph: To many people outside Gaza, the war flashes by as a doomscroll of headlines and casualty tolls and photos of screaming children, the bloody shreds of somebody else’s anguish.
articles.byline: By Vivian Yee, Abu Bakr Bashir and Gaya Gupta

articles.headline: Taylor Swift, Travis Kelce and a MAGA Meltdown
articles.snippet: The fulminations surrounding the world’s biggest pop icon — and girlfriend of Chiefs tight end Travis Kelce — reached the stratosphere after Kansas City made it to the Super Bowl.
articles.abstract: The fulminations surrounding the world’s biggest pop icon — and girlfriend of Chiefs tight end Travis Kelce — reached the stratosphere after Kansas City made it to the Super Bowl.
articles.lead_paragraph: For football fans eager to see a new team in the Super Bowl, the conference championship games on Sunday that sent the Kansas City Chiefs and San Francisco 49ers back to the main event of American sports culture were sorely disappointing.
